OL,3,CWatchdog warns of 'national security
OL,4,Cthreat' from drone drug drops to jails
OL,6,F"Drugs are a destructive force in
OL,7,Fprisons. Where there is drug abuse,
OL,8,Fthere is also debt and violence.
OL,9,FPrevious governments have spent
OL,10,Fmillions trying to tighten security,
OL,11,Fbut in Long Lartin and Manchester we
OL,12,Fcan see how far that goes.
OL,14,F"The best way to stop the supply of
OL,15,Fdrugs into jails is to reduce the
OL,16,Fdemand for them in the first place.
OL,17,FThis means ensuring that people are
OL,18,Foccupied with work, training,
OL,19,Feducation and exercise, not stuck in
OL,20,Ffilthy, rat-infested cells for hours
OL,21,Fon end."
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOU}D@HO]
